OL,6,FIn the little spare time she has,
OL,7,F16-year-old Daria Fesun paints
OL,8,Fpictures. The rainbow-coloured
OL,9,Fstill-lifes of vases filled with
OL,10,Fsunflowers and corn distance her from
OL,11,Fthe dismal reality of a year of war in
OL,12,FZaporizhzhia, Ukraine.
OL,14,FEvery day, Daria studies online at
OL,15,Fhome. Air raid alarms interrupt her
OL,16,Flessons, sometimes several times a day.
OL,17,FThen she and her younger sister shelter
OL,18,Fin a corridor, often for an hour or
OL,19,Flonger.
OL,3,CHow 'heroic' Ukrainian children are
OL,4,Cresisting Russia
